# research_notebook/ — personal sandbox + GIGANTIC's own AI infrastructure sandbox.
# Per gigantic_project-COPYME/ai/ai_FYIs/gigantic_conventions.md §1, §9, §25, §59.
#
# What ships:
#   - This .gitignore
#   - README.md at any depth in research_ai/ (project-wide doc-ships
#     convention). Inside research_user/, README is suppressed by
#     default so user prose stays local.
#   - .gitkeep at any depth (preserves per-subproject directory
#     structure for git in both research_ai/ and research_user/)
#   - GIGANTIC toolkits (per §59) — NextFlow workflows developed in
#     research_user/ and explicitly re-included via toolkit exceptions
#     below. Currently: ncbi_genomes-gigantic_T1_toolkit/ under
#     subproject-genomesDB/.
#
# What does NOT ship:
#   - research_user/** — personal sandbox; ships ONLY the
#     per-subproject .gitkeep placeholders unless a specific path is
#     re-included as a §59 toolkit.
#   - research_ai/sessions/*.jsonl.gz — captured session transcripts
#     (gitignored by the catch-all below; never edited / deleted)
#   - research_ai/sessions/TRANSCRIPT_CAPTURE_LOG.md — per-project local
#     capture log (also caught by the catch-all)
#   - Any other personal content (notes, draft analyses, downloaded data)

# Default: ignore everything in this tree
*

# Allow traversal into subdirectories (so the rules below can match)
!*/

# Keep this .gitignore
!.gitignore

# Keep README.md at any depth (project-wide doc-ships convention)
!README.md

# Keep .gitkeep stubs at any depth (preserves per-subproject directory
# structure for git, including subproject-<X>/.gitkeep placeholders)
!.gitkeep
!**/.gitkeep

# research_user/ defaults to personal sandbox per §25 — by default
# ships ONLY the per-subproject .gitkeep placeholders so users have
# pre-materialized subproject-<X>/ directories. README.md is suppressed
# inside research_user/ so user prose stays local. Specific paths may
# be re-included as toolkits (per §59).
research_user/**
# Re-include subproject-* directories so git can descend into them.
# Per git docs: "It is not possible to re-include a file if a parent
# directory of that file is excluded." So we must un-ignore the dirs
# (trailing slash = directory match) BEFORE re-including files inside.
!research_user/subproject-*/
!research_user/subproject-*/**/
# Allow the per-subproject .gitkeep placeholders at any depth
!research_user/.gitkeep
!research_user/**/.gitkeep

# §59 toolkit exception: ncbi_genomes-gigantic_T1_toolkit/ is a
# GIGANTIC "toolkit" — a NextFlow workflow developed during GIGANTIC
# work that users can optionally run OUTSIDE gigantic subprojects.
# This one downloads/processes NCBI reference genomes (GCFs) to produce
# T1 proteomes required as user-provided input for the genomesDB
# subproject. Tracked in full; x_* backups inside still ignored by the
# x_* rule below.
!research_user/subproject-genomesDB/ncbi_genomes-gigantic_T1_toolkit/**

# Archive directories: anything starting with x_ is a disposable archive
# and must stay ignored even if it contains files that would otherwise
# be tracked (including x_* backups inside a toolkit). Place AFTER all
# exceptions so this rule wins for x_-prefixed paths.
x_*
**/x_*
